<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA General Task//EN" "generalTask.dtd">
<task id="task_zn4_qrn_25">
    <title>Configuring Data Collector with Cloudera Manager</title>
    <shortdesc>When administering <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> with
        Cloudera Manager, configure all <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
        configuration properties and environment variables through Cloudera Manager. </shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>Manual changes to <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> configuration files can be overwritten by Cloudera Manager. </p>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_tvq_xsn_25">
            <step>
                <cmd>In Cloudera Manager, select the <uicontrol>StreamSets</uicontrol> service, then
                    click <uicontrol>Configuration</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                <info>The <wintitle>Configuration</wintitle> page displays <ph
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                    /> configuration properties. </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>On the <wintitle>Configuration</wintitle> page, in the navigation panel, you
                    can select a category to configure related properties. </cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
    <related-links>
        <link href="DCConfig.dita#concept_pq5_xjq_kr"/>
        <link href="DCEnvironmentConfig.dita#concept_rng_qym_qr"/>
    </related-links>
</task>
